      "side": 1,
      "message": "This function can\u0027t be private. It\u0027s used by the helper class GLCircularRRectEffect in emitCode:\n\n```\n    SkString inputSample \u003d (crre.getInputFPIndex() \u003e\u003d 0)\n                ? this-\u003einvokeChild(crre.getInputFPIndex(), args.fInputColor, args)\n                : SkString(args.fInputColor);\n```\n\nI can change it to `bool hasInputFP()` and change emitCode to do:\n\n```\n    SkString inputSample \u003d crre.hasInputFP()\n                ? this-\u003einvokeChild(/*childIndex\u003d*/0, args.fInputColor, args)\n                : SkString(args.fInputColor);\n```\n\nTo me this is just 6 of one and half dozen of the other. :) If you prefer the second form, SGTM.\n\n(Technically I could make these two classes friends and then avoid a getter, but the normal pattern I\u0027ve seen for these sets of paired classes has been getter functions, not friendship. Usually friend is a last-resort kind of option.)",
